The paper deals with the problem of distributed data acquisition, which is a topic that falls under the sub-categories of information theory (cs.IT), machine learning (cs.LG), signal processing (cs.SP), scientific computing (cs.NA), and systems and control (cs.SI). The paper specifically discusses the use of Lasso and Group-Lasso estimators, which are commonly used in machine learning and signal processing. Additionally, the application to wireless sensor networks falls under the systems and control sub-category. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.IT, cs.LG, and cs.SP, followed by cs.SI and cs.NA.
